%% styling_language

## Styling Conventions

- Do not introduce Tailwind CSS or utility-class frameworks.
- Only use semantic CSS defined in global or shared {styling_language} files.
- CSS classes specific to a component or island must be prefixed with the component name in `slug-case`
%%% framework=Fresh
  (`HeaderMenu.{component_extension}` => `.header-menu`, `.header-menu-button`, `.header-menu-button-text`).
%%%
- Use unitless values for line heights.
- Use rem values for font sizes and all other static sizes (only multiples of 0.1rem or 0.25rem).
- Use px values only for tiny static sizes (i.e. 1px or 2px).
- Use maximum one decimal in your sizes (1rem, 2.5rem), unless for multiple of 0.25rem.
- Use standard section comments to group CSS rules by category:
  - `// -- IMPORTS`
  - `// -- CONSTANTS`
  - `// -- VARIABLES`
  - `// -- FUNCTIONS`
  - `// -- MIXINS`
  - `// -- FONTS` (for @font-face definitions)
  - `// -- ELEMENTS`
  - `// -- CLASSES`
